          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
            <div class="full-width-content">
            <Accordion variant='splitted' title="Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) – Whirlpool Washer Repair">
              <AccordionItem title="Why won't my Whirlpool washer spin?">
                <p>This could be due to a worn drive belt, a faulty lid switch, or a control board issue. Our techs can quickly diagnose the root cause.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="My washer is leaking water—what's the issue?">
                <p>Leaks may come from damaged door gaskets, worn tub seals, or loose hoses. We inspect all components for a precise repair.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="How do I know if it's time to replace my Whirlpool washer?">
                <p>If your washer is over 12 years old and needs a costly part like a drum or control board, replacement might be worth considering. We'll give you honest advice.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="What's the typical lifespan of a Whirlpool washer?">
                <p>With proper care, Whirlpool washers can last 10–14 years. Regular maintenance and timely repairs help extend this lifespan.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="Do you carry parts for same-day repairs?">
